I want to write a package that provides a custom cursor. The method for doing this in LESS is to have a `cursor` attribute:

``` less
.foo {
  cursor: url(my-custom-cursor.svg) 6 12, auto;
}
```

According to the CSS spec, URLs are relative to the stylesheet. The stylesheet in my package is in `~/.atom/packages/foo/stylesheets/foo.less`. But when I have the above LESS code, Atom reports that the asset was unable to be loaded from (on OS X) `/Applications/Atom.app/Contents/app/static/my-custom-cursor.svg`. I would expect the above (or some reasonable variant) to be able to work.
